The paper deals with the problem of identifying and estimating the joints of a robot arm using deep learning techniques, which is a core problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed involves training a multi-objective Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to identify the robot body in the image and estimate 3D positions of the joints by using just a 2D image, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning techniques to adapt the CNN to a new robot arm, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of industrial robotics, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
